&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Pharmacist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Pharmacist to participate in our training rotation providing a wide variety of experience including surgical, acute admissions and emergency medicine, orthopaedics, paediatrics; medicines information and aseptic services. Whatever your ambitions, our personalised clinical training programme will develop your medicine optimisation skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your clinical work will include inpatient medication history taking on admission; medicines reconciliation; the formulation of pharmaceutical care plans; patient counselling; electronic discharge management, and undertaking audit projects and drug use review&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your development will be supported by a clinical supervisor and you will be provided with all the skills and knowledge to progress a career in hospital pharmacy plus the opportunity to study for a postgraduate clinical diploma in pharmacy practice and to undertake an independent pharmacist prescriber course&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you flexible working arrangements and we are committed to your personal development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Weekend and bank holiday working and participation in the on-call service is expected&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 1 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Bernice Abrahams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Principle Pharmacist Clinical Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address bernice.abrahams@tgh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phone: 0161 922 4813 &lt;/p&gt;
